18/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- At a ceremony Wednesday (17 September), US Ambassador to Croatia Ralph Frank delivered equipment worth 101,000 euros to the interior ministry. The protective clothing and a computer simulator for small arms use will be used to help train Croatian police.
Also Wednesday, representatives of the Croatian Labour and Social Welfare Ministry and the International Organisation for Migration signed an agreement on co-operation in human trafficking prevention. It envisions providing shelter and other assistance to victims of human trafficking, as well as information exchanges.
In other news, Prime Minister Ivica Racan and his Polish counterpart, Leszek Miller, signed an agreement on protecting classified information. Meeting in Zagreb on Wednesday, the two agreed there are no unresolved issues between their countries. (HINA, PAP, BBC - 17/09/03)
